### Problem13

Functions, which are known as _____(0)\___ _____(1)\___ in java, are important because they allow us to clearly separate tasks within a program and because they provide general mechanism that enables us to reuse code (literally from sec-2.1).

Look at the following code:

```java
1   public static double harmonic (int n)
2   {
3       double sum =0.0
4       for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) sum += 1.0/i;
5       return sum;
6   }
```

The first line is called a _____(2)\___ of the function. The "double" in the first line is called the _____(3)\___ _____(4)\___ of the function (literally from an image of sec-2.1). Can we use the "sum" defined in the harmonic function in our main() method? Answer:_____(5)\___ (y/n).

